---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="FraiseQL Community - Get Help, Contribute, Connect"
  description="Join the FraiseQL community. Get help, contribute to open source, and connect with other developers."
>
  <div style="padding: 2rem; max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto;">
    <h1>🤝 Community</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; color: #666;">
      <strong>Join the FraiseQL community and help shape the future of database-first GraphQL</strong>
    </p>

    <section style="margin: 3rem 0;">
      <h2>Get Help</h2>
      <p>Multiple channels for support depending on your needs:</p>

      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0;">
        <div style="padding: 1.5rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb; border-radius: 8px;">
          <h3>GitHub Issues</h3>
          <p style="color: #666; margin: 0.5rem 0;">Bug reports and feature requests</p>
          <a href="https://github.com/fraiseql/fraiseql/issues">Open Issues →</a>
        </div>

        <div style="padding: 1.5rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb; border-radius: 8px;">
          <h3>GitHub Discussions</h3>
          <p style="color: #666; margin: 0.5rem 0;">Questions, ideas, and general discussion</p>
          <a href="https://github.com/fraiseql/fraiseql/discussions">Join Discussions →</a>
        </div>

        <div style="padding: 1.5rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb; border-radius: 8px;">
          <h3>Email Support</h3>
          <p style="color: #666; margin: 0.5rem 0;">Enterprise and commercial support</p>
          <p><a href="mailto:support@fraiseql.dev">support@fraiseql.dev</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 3rem 0;">
      <h2>Contributing</h2>
      <p>
        FraiseQL is open source and welcomes contributions from the community. Whether you're fixing bugs, adding features, or improving documentation, there's a place for you.
      </p>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">How to Get Started</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <strong>Read the Contributing Guide:</strong>
          <br />
          <a href="https://github.com/fraiseql/fraiseql/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md">
            CONTRIBUTING.md
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Find a Good First Issue:</strong>
          <br />
          <a href="https://github.com/fraiseql/fraiseql/issues?q=is%3Aopen+label%3A%22good+first+issue%22">
            Browse good first issues
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Understand the Architecture:</strong>
          <br />
          <a href="https://github.com/fraiseql/fraiseql/blob/main/.claude/ARCHITECTURE_PRINCIPLES.md">
            Architecture Principles
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Development Setup:</strong>
          <br />
          <a href="https://github.com/fraiseql/fraiseql/blob/main/.claude/CLAUDE.md">
            Development Guide
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Submit Your Pull Request:</strong>
          <br />
          Follow the TDD discipline: RED → GREEN → REFACTOR → CLEANUP
        </li>
      </ol>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Code Quality Standards</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>All Rust code must pass <code>cargo clippy</code> with pedantic + deny</li>
        <li>No <code>unsafe</code> code allowed (except in rare justified cases)</li>
        <li>All tests must pass: <code>cargo test</code></li>
        <li>100% type safety required</li>
        <li>Comprehensive documentation for public APIs</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 3rem 0;">
      <h2>Learning Resources</h2>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Documentation</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong><a href="/how-it-works">How It Works</a></strong> – 3-stage compilation pipeline explained
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong><a href="/ecosystem">Ecosystem Overview</a></strong> – All 11 tools and their integration
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong><a href="/verification">Verification Registry</a></strong> – All claims backed by proof
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong><a href="https://github.com/fraiseql/fraiseql/tree/main/docs">Official Docs</a></strong> – Complete API and architecture reference
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Examples</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong><a href="https://github.com/fraiseql/fraiseql/tree/main/examples">50+ Examples</a></strong> – Runnable projects demonstrating features
        </li>
        <li>Blog API – Authentication, queries, mutations</li>
        <li>E-Commerce API – Complex relationships, inventory management</li>
        <li>SaaS Platform – Multi-tenant isolation, RBAC</li>
        <li>Analytics Dashboard – Arrow Flight, materialized views</li>
        <li>Compliance Demo – Audit logging, encryption</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Real-World Applications</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/use-cases/regulated-industries">Regulated Industries</a> – HIPAA, PCI-DSS, SOC 2</li>
        <li><a href="/use-cases/enterprise-saas">Enterprise SaaS</a> – Multi-tenant platforms</li>
        <li><a href="/use-cases/analytics">Analytics</a> – Real-time dashboards</li>
        <li><a href="/use-cases/e-commerce">E-Commerce</a> – Complex product relationships</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 3rem 0;">
      <h2>Roadmap & Releases</h2>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Current Status</h3>
      <p>
        <strong>Version 2.0.0-alpha.1</strong> – Production-ready with layered optionality. All core features complete.
      </p>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Upcoming</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>v2.0.0-beta: Extended testing and stabilization</li>
        <li>v2.0.0-stable: General availability</li>
        <li>Enhanced observability (v2.1.0)</li>
        <li>Additional database backends (v2.2.0)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Follow Updates</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href="https://github.com/fraiseql/fraiseql/releases">
            GitHub Releases
          </a> – New versions and features
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://github.com/fraiseql/fraiseql/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md">
            Changelog
          </a> – Detailed version history
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://github.com/fraiseql/fraiseql">
            GitHub Repository
          </a> – Watch for updates
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 3rem 0;">
      <h2>Community Standards</h2>
      <p>
        We're committed to maintaining a welcoming, inclusive community. Please review our code of conduct:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Be respectful and inclusive</li>
        <li>Focus on technical merit</li>
        <li>Help others learn and grow</li>
        <li>Report violations to the maintainers</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 3rem 0;">
      <h2>Recognition</h2>
      <p>
        Contributors are recognized in the project repository and community. Whether you fix a typo or implement a major feature, your contributions matter.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="https://github.com/fraiseql/fraiseql/graphs/contributors">
          View all contributors →
        </a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">
      <a href="/">← Back to Home</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
